{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M8cbwdCB755B2LJUXRzLfW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Ralph Fix Plan\n     2→\n     3→## High Priority (Bugs)\n     4→\n     5→- [x] #2 - Replace unsafe `unwrap()` calls with proper error handling in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n     6→  - Replaced 4x `serde_json::to_value().unwrap()` with `map_err` in analyze endpoints\n     7→  - Replaced 2x `.as_ref().unwrap()` with `.ok_or(...)` in `clean_file`\n     8→- [x] #7 - Fix temp file memory leak from `Box::leak()` in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n     9→  - Added `temp_paths: Vec<PathBuf>` to `AppState` with `Drop` impl for cleanup\n    10→  - Replaced `Box::leak`/`mem::forget` with `tmp_path.keep()` + tracking in state\n    11→\n    12→## High Priority (Code Quality)\n    13→\n    14→- [x] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n    15→  - Added tracing + tracing-subscriber deps, initialized in main()\n    16→  - Replaced gui/mod.rs println with tracing::info!, config/manager.rs eprintln with tracing::warn!\n    17→  - Note: src/ui/ and src/inspect/ println calls are intentional CLI user output, not logging\n    18→\n    19→## Medium Priority (Features - Backend)\n    20→\n    21→- [x] #6 - Expose FLAC and AAC format support in CLI\n    22→  - Added `flac` feature to symphonia, added Flac/Aac variants to AudioFormat\n    23→  - Generalized load_mp3 into load_symphonia for all symphonia-decoded formats\n    24→  - No FLAC/AAC encoders available; pipeline auto-falls back to WAV output\n    25→  - Updated sweep/benchmark default extensions to include flac/aac/m4a\n    26→- [x] #12 - Add `--dry-run` flag to clean command\n    27→  - Added `--dry-run` flag to Clean command in CLI\n    28→  - Runs full detection/analysis then exits before sanitization pipeline\n    29→- [x] #13 - Add export report feature (JSON and PDF)\n    30→  - Added `--report <path>` flag to both `clean` and `detect` commands\n    31→  - Exports JSON with file info, watermark, metadata, statistical, polez, and sanitization results\n    32→  - Made serde_json a non-optional dep; re-exported detection result types\n    33→  - PDF deferred (no easy pure-Rust PDF crate)\n    34→- [x] #19 - Add streaming support for large audio files\n    35→  - Added split_chunks/join_chunks to AudioBuffer with overlap-add crossfading\n    36→  - Pipeline auto-switches to chunked mode for files >5M samples (~60s at 44.1kHz)\n    37→  - Chunks: ~30s with 1s overlap, crossfaded back together after processing\n    38→  - Original buffer dropped before chunk processing to reduce peak memory\n    39→\n    40→## Medium Priority (Features - GUI)\n    41→\n    42→- [x] #1 - Add spectrogram visualization for cleaned audio\n    43→  - Extracted `compute_spectrogram` helper from `get_spectrogram` to avoid duplication\n    44→  - Added `/api/spectrogram/cleaned` endpoint using cleaned_buffer from state\n    45→  - Frontend rendering deferred to a separate frontend-focused issue\n    46→- [ ] #5 - Add upload progress indicator and file size validation\n    47→  - Frontend: show upload progress bar, validate max file size before upload\n    48→  - Backend: already has 500MB limit, surface it to frontend\n    49→- [ ] #10 - Display verification results and quality scores in GUI\n    50→- [ ] #11 - Add configuration and preset selection UI\n    51→- [ ] #14 - Add audio playback controls in GUI\n    52→- [ ] #9 - Add before/after audio comparison timeline\n    53→- [ ] #20 - Add detailed metadata tag viewer in GUI\n    54→\n    55→## Low Priority (Infrastructure)\n    56→\n    57→- [ ] #3 - Implement comprehensive test suite\n    58→  - Unit tests for detection modules, sanitization pipeline, DSP primitives\n    59→  - Integration tests for CLI commands\n    60→- [ ] #16 - Add React error boundaries for component crashes\n    61→- [ ] #8 - Add session persistence across page refreshes\n    62→- [ ] #17 - Add code coverage reporting (CI)\n    63→- [ ] #15 - Add release artifact publishing on git tags (CI)\n    64→- [ ] #18 - Optimize spectral operations to reuse STFT computations\n    65→\n    66→## Completed\n    67→- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n    68→\n    69→## Working Notes\n    70→- All issues sourced from GitHub issues list (as of 2026-03-10)\n    71→- Issues labeled `ralph-task`: #2, #3, #4, #6, #7, #12, #15, #16, #17, #18\n    72→- After completing an issue, run `gh issue close <number>` to close it\n    73→- Always run `cargo check --all-targets && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo fmt --all --check` before committing\n    74→- Commit format: conventional commits, single line, no co-authorship trailers\n    75→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9bd7957-c8f2-4e48-8fcc-7059d242854c","uuid":"afc445af-f30c-400a-a891-d5f3c5c006c1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/.ralph/fix_plan.md","content":"# Ralph Fix Plan\n\n## High Priority (Bugs)\n\n- [x] #2 - Replace unsafe `unwrap()` calls with proper error handling in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n  - Replaced 4x `serde_json::to_value().unwrap()` with `map_err` in analyze endpoints\n  - Replaced 2x `.as_ref().unwrap()` with `.ok_or(...)` in `clean_file`\n- [x] #7 - Fix temp file memory leak from `Box::leak()` in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n  - Added `temp_paths: Vec<PathBuf>` to `AppState` with `Drop` impl for cleanup\n  - Replaced `Box::leak`/`mem::forget` with `tmp_path.keep()` + tracking in state\n\n## High Priority (Code Quality)\n\n- [x] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n  - Added tracing + tracing-subscriber deps, initialized in main()\n  - Replaced gui/mod.rs println with tracing::info!, config/manager.rs eprintln with tracing::warn!\n  - Note: src/ui/ and src/inspect/ println calls are intentional CLI user output, not logging\n\n## Medium Priority (Features - Backend)\n\n- [x] #6 - Expose FLAC and AAC format support in CLI\n  - Added `flac` feature to symphonia, added Flac/Aac variants to AudioFormat\n  - Generalized load_mp3 into load_symphonia for all symphonia-decoded formats\n  - No FLAC/AAC encoders available; pipeline auto-falls back to WAV output\n  - Updated sweep/benchmark default extensions to include flac/aac/m4a\n- [x] #12 - Add `--dry-run` flag to clean command\n  - Added `--dry-run` flag to Clean command in CLI\n  - Runs full detection/analysis then exits before sanitization pipeline\n- [x] #13 - Add export report feature (JSON and PDF)\n  - Added `--report <path>` flag to both `clean` and `detect` commands\n  - Exports JSON with file info, watermark, metadata, statistical, polez, and sanitization results\n  - Made serde_json a non-optional dep; re-exported detection result types\n  - PDF deferred (no easy pure-Rust PDF crate)\n- [x] #19 - Add streaming support for large audio files\n  - Added split_chunks/join_chunks to AudioBuffer with overlap-add crossfading\n  - Pipeline auto-switches to chunked mode for files >5M samples (~60s at 44.1kHz)\n  - Chunks: ~30s with 1s overlap, crossfaded back together after processing\n  - Original buffer dropped before chunk processing to reduce peak memory\n\n## Medium Priority (Features - GUI)\n\n- [x] #1 - Add spectrogram visualization for cleaned audio\n  - Extracted `compute_spectrogram` helper from `get_spectrogram` to avoid duplication\n  - Added `/api/spectrogram/cleaned` endpoint using cleaned_buffer from state\n  - Frontend rendering deferred to a separate frontend-focused issue\n- [ ] #5 - Add upload progress indicator and file size validation\n  - Frontend: show upload progress bar, validate max file size before upload\n  - Backend: already has 500MB limit, surface it to frontend\n- [ ] #10 - Display verification results and quality scores in GUI\n- [ ] #11 - Add configuration and preset selection UI\n- [ ] #14 - Add audio playback controls in GUI\n- [ ] #9 - Add before/after audio comparison timeline\n- [ ] #20 - Add detailed metadata tag viewer in GUI\n\n## Low Priority (Infrastructure)\n\n- [ ] #3 - Implement comprehensive test suite\n  - Unit tests for detection modules, sanitization pipeline, DSP primitives\n  - Integration tests for CLI commands\n- [ ] #16 - Add React error boundaries for component crashes\n- [ ] #8 - Add session persistence across page refreshes\n- [ ] #17 - Add code coverage reporting (CI)\n- [ ] #15 - Add release artifact publishing on git tags (CI)\n- [ ] #18 - Optimize spectral operations to reuse STFT computations\n\n## Completed\n- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n\n## Working Notes\n- All issues sourced from GitHub issues list (as of 2026-03-10)\n- Issues labeled `ralph-task`: #2, #3, #4, #6, #7, #12, #15, #16, #17, #18\n- After completing an issue, run `gh issue close <number>` to close it\n- Always run `cargo check --all-targets && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo fmt --all --check` before committing\n- Commit format: conventional commits, single line, no co-authorship trailers\n","numLines":75,"startLine":1,"totalLines":75}}}
